Another major difficulty is that all errors, be it client side exceptions on handling the request or even the response, as well as server side faults, are all wrapped by CXF as soap faults with terse error messages making it very difficult to understand what&#39;s really happening. The only way left that allowed me to progress was assembling needed client code in a POJO and debugging it with help of CXF and WSS4J source code libraries( Eclipse/Maven fetches the source code for you while you use the debugger and drill down... efficient!)

