You check for it, within the _main_ loop.

```java
if (board.board[row][col] == &#39; &#39;)
```

I used the _[Arrays#fill](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/20/docs/api/java.base/java/util/Arrays.html#fill(char[],char))_ method here, to avoid having to write another loop.  
And I added it to the default constructor.&amp;nbsp; You could technically use the _[initialization block](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/javaOO/initial.html)_, as well.

```java
Board() {
    for (char[] row : board) Arrays.fill(row, &#39; &#39;);
}
```

